I am a 26 Year Old Teacher from NYC, I am Wiccan and love to RP, but only if it mature Storylines, and by mature, I do not mean perverted. If you are looking to bother me for sick sexual reasons, dont waste your time.  I enjoy horsebackriding, Ice skating, going for long walks int he woods with my soulmate whome I am deeply in love with. I am an animal lover as well. I enjoy books rather to TV...Rare, isnt it. My favorite author is Laurell K Hamilton. I enjoy all types of music, except Country...nothing against it, just cant get into it.
Any other questions about me...feel free to ask.</span></div> 		<div id="personalbio"><span class="title">Personal Bio ::</span> <span class="value">Morrigan
Celtic Goddess of Death, War and Rebirth.
Triple Goddess
My name translating to Phantom Queen.
During the times of war, I appear in the form of  a Raven
I helped defeat the Firbolgs at the First Battle of Magh Tuireadh and the Fomorii at the Second Battle of Mag Tured.
I am the consort of Dagda.We meet on Samhain to consumate.

My origins  reach directly back to the megalithic cult of the Mothers. The Mothers (Matrones, Idises, Dísir, etc.) usually appeared as triple goddesses and their cult was expressed through both battle ecstasy and regenerative ecstasy. Later Celtic goddesses of sovereignty, such as the trio of Éire, Banba, and Fótla, also use magic in warfare. "Influence in the sphere of warfare, but by means of magic and incantation rather than through physical strength, is common to these beings."
----------------------------------
Attributes: archetypal Goddess of war, death and passionate love. 
Representation: 
as a black raven or crow, who feeds on the killed warriors after battle. 
Relations: Wife or Lover of Dagda. Mother of Brigid, Goddess of the Sacred Flame of Kildare
Offerings: Blood sacrifice
----------------------------------
